results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Taupe Blue
Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Cinder'
results.story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black
results.story: Kanye teased the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Black’ colorway in a February 2015 interview with New York’s Power 105.1 FM. Later he was spotted wearing a black suede/gum sole iteration of the sneaker at a Givenchy show during New York Fashion Week. Released on December 19, 2015, as the second colorway of the Yeezy Boost 750 line, the ‘Black’ sneaker features a full suede upper, perforated vamp, and ankle zipper.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Infant ‘Cloud White’ presents the debut colorway of a futuristic Yeezy model scaled down for little feet. Decorative no-tie stretch laces are integrated into the flexible knit upper, featuring an elastic cuff for a sock-like fit. A molded EVA midsole combines with an Ortholite sockliner to deliver lightweight cushioning, while its unique structure forms a supportive cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a wavy traction pattern for added grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Yecoraite Reflective (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Yecoraite’ offers sock-like comfort for little feet, featuring a Primeknit upper equipped with decorative no-tie laces and a snug, elastic collar. A blend of grey and off-white tones is contrasted by a translucent monofilament window in a diluted orange hue. The minimalist silhouette sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, enveloped in a semi-translucent rubber cage and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole in a subtle coral finish.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Mist Non-Reflective’ features a breathable Primeknit upper finished in varying grey shades that form an all-over camo-like pattern. An elastic collar delivers a snug fit, while perforated detailing increases ventilation on the side panel, which is further highlighted by a semi-translucent patch of tan coloring. The tooling consists of a responsive Boost midsole, reinforced with a durable gum rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum
results.story: The Air Yeezy 2 NRG 'Pure Platinum' launched in June 2012 featuring a subdued colorway that blends varying shades of grey on the upper and a contrasting pop of bright red on the collar lining. The unique design allows it to straddle the line between fashion and sport. The snakeskin texture on the side panels and prominent ridges on the molded rubber heel serve to elevate the design, but the Air Tech Challenge II midsole keeps the shoe grounded in the heritage of the Swoosh.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘LMNTE Reflective’ adds a hi-vis element to Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, featuring slip-on construction designed to hug the foot in lightweight support. Reflective threads are woven into the mostly brown Primeknit upper, accented with mustard yellow coloring throughout the translucent monofilament window. The minimalist build is mounted atop a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent cage for added durability. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Asia Pacific, Africa, the Middle East, and India.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Clay'
results.story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper Reflective’ offers sock-like comfort on the upper, crafted from subtly patterned Primeknit in a blend of light grey and beige hues. Reflective fibers are woven into the mix, offering enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A coppery finish distinguishes the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, adding a see-through element to the minimalist build. A greyish-blue rubber cage envelops the full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (Infant)
results.story: Released on August 24th, 2016, alongside the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 colorway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Turtle Dove’ is an exact replica of the adult model in infant sizes from 5 to 10. The design features a blue-gray/turtle dove Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a white Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core Black
results.story: Designed by Kanye West, the Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas 'Core Black' is a minimalist take on adidas' Powerphase sneaker from the 80s. Dressed in an all-black leather upper with matching laces, the lateral side is accented by gold ‘Calabasas’ print and green 'adidas' text alongside a red Trefoil logo. A black EVA midsole and rubber outsole complete the look. Released as part of the 'Calabasas' collection, other colorways include 'Core White' and 'Grey'.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Alien Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Alien Blue’ delivers a wintry colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a grey and cream Primeknit upper with reflective detailing for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A subtle green finish distinguishes the monofilament window that adds textural depth to the sneaker’s lateral side panel. The sock-like build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent blue rubber cage and supported by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ offers a subdued colorway of the minimalist silhouette, featuring a composition of black and dark brown fibers that make up the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is interrupted on the sneaker’s lateral side, where a post dyed monofilament side stripe sweeps through the midfoot. A smokey rubber cage envelops the Boost midsole, visible through cut-outs in the gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Mist'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sesame
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sesame’ features a refined color palette that complements the shoe’s minimalist build. The breathable Primeknit upper keeps the heel tab and distinct center stitch detailing but loses the mirrored ‘SPLY-350’ branding. Underneath, a semi-translucent rubber midsole houses a full-length Boost cushioning, while a gum rubber outsole delivers enhanced traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kids ‘Alvah’ features a subdued color scheme, highlighted by a black monofilament mesh upper with flowing grey stripes. An exoskeletal overlay in glow-in-the-dark RPU provides structure to the sneaker’s side panels, while a rubberized toe cap is good for lightweight durability. Reflective detailing offers added visibility at the base of the tongue. In lieu of Boost cushioning, the sneaker uses a bulky EVA midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an energetic color scheme made up of yellow and tan hues throughout the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is treated to a green-tinged glow-in-the-dark finish, matching the dayglow shade applied to the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window. The bright tones are tempered by the midsole, featuring full-length Boost encased in dark grey rubber. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Bright Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Bright Blue’ uses sharply contrasting finishes to delineate the lifestyle runner’s upper and tooling. The latter pairs sculpted orange sidewalls with a contrasting black rubber outsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern with cut-out detailing that reveals a drop-in Boost midsole. Up top, royal blue mesh is reinforced with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel, along with black suede midfoot panels enlivened with reflective detailing.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Synth'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Synth' sneaker is characterized by minimalist design principles and progressive cues as envisioned by Kanye West. Regionally launched in June 2019, this edition's duo-tone Primeknit upper features patterned rope laces and a transparent stripe on the lateral side. Three-Stripes detailing is seen at the interior heel. A Boost-encapsulated tubular sole optimizes impact support.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Frozen Blue’ injects a vibrant dose of color to the basketball-inspired silhouette, highlighted by a bright blue RPU cage overlaid across the jacquard knit upper. Black neoprene is utilized on the collar and tongue to deliver a comfortable fit, while a seamless heel counter provides rearfoot stability. The mid-top rides on a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent TPU cage and reinforced with a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Carbon’ features a breathable Primeknit upper in a neutral black and grey finish. The sneaker’s lateral side features a streak of black via the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, separating a light grey weave up top with mostly black construction on the lower half. No-tie bungee laces deliver a secure fit. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a yellow-tinged rubber cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ utilizes a sock-like Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of beige and orange tones. The sneaker’s signature translucent monofilament window stands out in a contrasting blue finish, complete with perforated detailing for improved breathability. The one-piece build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a semi-translucent cage and reinforced by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids pulls iconic technology from the German brand's archives, packaging them into a retro-influenced sneaker driven by Kanye West's design ethos. Arrived in August 2019, this edition is crafted of Bone White mesh, cow suede and leather. Reinforced laces and reflective piping around the eyelets hint at a utilitarian aesthetic. An AdiPRENE+ midsole and rubber outsole supply cushioning and grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM BSKTBL Frozen Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Basketball ‘Frozen Blue’ highlights a pop of color on the performance-ready version of Kanye West’s futuristic hoops shoe. The upper features textile knit construction reinforced with RPU overlays, their raised wavy lines traced with vibrant blue coloring. Extra padding is added to the black neoprene collar, reinforced with a seamless heel counter that extends to a full-length Boost midsole encaged in semi-translucent TPU. Underfoot, a herringbone traction rubber outsole provides optimal grip on the hardwood.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2015)
results.story: Released on August 22nd, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Pirate Black’ features a pirate black/dark gray Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Reflective’ makes use of a Primeknit upper in a blend of orange and brown hues, resulting in a unique camo-like pattern that’s enlivened with a contrasting pop of blue on the translucent monofilament window. Reflective thread is woven into the sock-like build, offering added visibility in low-light conditions. The responsive Boost midsole is encased in semi-translucent rubber and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 'Vanta' was offered up in this infant-sized iteration for a June 2019 release. The shoe features a futuristic, multi-layer mesh upper with suede overlays, just like the larger sizes. The Yeezy 700 V2 features a similar chunky midsole compared to the V1, which debuted at Kanye West's Season 5 fashion show in 2017. The midsole houses full-length adidas Boost cushioning for responsive comfort.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Infant)
results.story: Debuting in late March, 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Clay' marked the first time a 350 would be released in adult, kids and infant sizes. The infant-sized Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Clay' mimics the larger versions, with a Primeknit upper that features a variety of patterns in orange-brown with a horizontal contrast stripe. A bright orange heel tab adds an accent, and the silhouette sits atop a translucent midsole and rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Carbon’ delivers a neutral colorway of the slip-on sneaker, secured with no-tie bungee laces for a snug fit. The upper makes use of breathable Primeknit in a mostly black finish with varying shades of grey throughout. On the lateral side, a black monofilament side stripe cuts through the two-tone woven paneling. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, encased entirely in semi-translucent rubber.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Zyon’ delivers a neutral colorway of Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, highlighted by complementary grey and brown tones on a stretchy Primeknit upper. Traditional lace closure enhances the fit of the slip-on silhouette, while a black monofilament side stripe provides added breathability. The lightweight build rests on a full-length Boost midsole, visible through cut-out detailing on the rubber midsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Citrin Non-Reflective'
results.story: Defining an era, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is the manifestation of Kanye West's unique design methodology and cultural influence. This 'Citrin' version—launched in September 2019—carries a dual-tone Primeknit bootie and tonal cord laces. Translucent monofilament panels are inserted into the sides while the back heel pull is removed for this colorway. Its distinctive TPU ribbed rubber sole, encasing Boost cushioning, is updated with a contrast tread pattern.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Kids)
results.story: Issued in May 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 GID Kids 'Glow' sneaker remixes the unconventional icon with updated functionality. The Primeknit bootie illuminates in the dark as a result of a fluorescent green treatment. Rope laces, a signature heel pull and a translucent monofilament stripe on the lateral side give the shoe its distinctive look. Encased in a Tubular rubber sole, Boost technology helps improve energy return.

results.name: Air Yeezy 2 NRG 'Solar Red' Sample
results.story: The Air Yeezy 2 NRG ‘Solar Red’ may share a familiar color palette with its Air Yeezy ‘Blink’ predecessor, but the newer model stands out with a more refined silhouette, accented with special details crafted specifically for Kanye. They include a molded rubber heel, anaconda textured side panel, and Egyptology references on the tongue and midfoot strap. One feature carried over from the original Air Yeezy is the glow-in-the-dark outsole, utilized here on tooling lifted from the Nike Air Tech Challenge II. This is a sample shoe.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Cinder Reflective’ delivers a stealthy colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a Primeknit upper in a charcoal grey finish. The bootie-style construction of the collar is complemented by a pull tab for easy on and off, while the signature post-dyed side stripe is treated to a light-grabbing reflective finish for added visibility. A full-length Boost midsole, encased in a dark grey rubber cage, is visible through cut-outs in the gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black (Infant)
results.story: Following a limited February 2020 release exclusive to New York, London, and Tokyo, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Triple Black’ dropped in full family sizing roughly three months later, including this Infants edition for a new generation of Yeezy acolytes. The blacked-out sneaker features a polyester upper with reflective detailing, secured with no-tie bungee laces and supported by full-length drop-in Boost cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Infant ‘Phosphor’ showcases an eye-catching hue on the sneaker’s one-piece polyester upper. The high-visibility finish is augmented with reflective silver accents, including the oversized ‘700’ plastered across the sneaker’s lateral side panel. Under the foot, responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost unit, encapsulated within a black PU midsole and herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MXT Moon Gray
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Yecheil’ utilizes sharply contrasting hues throughout the sneaker’s re-engineered Primeknit upper, accented with a black monofilament stripe that bisects the side panel. Reflective thread is woven into the rope laces, adding a high-vis element to the miniaturized build. Responsive cushioning arrives via the sneaker’s full-length Boost midsole, visible through cut-out detailing in the black rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Kids 'Vanta' was released in June 2019, bringing an all-black look to the silhouette. This take arrives in youth sizing but retains the stand-out features of the adult style, with a multi-layered mesh upper and suede overlays. The sneaker houses responsive, full-length Boost cushioning within its distinctive chunky sole, a component which debuted on the 700 V1 at the Yeezy Season 5 show in 2017.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot House Blue (W)
adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Triple Black
results.story: Kanye West tapped industry legends Christian Tresser and Steven Smith for the adidas 700 MNVN. The sneaker's usual mixed-material profile is overhauled in favor of triple-black nylon designed with heat-welded panels and an enlarged 3M '700' graphic along the lateral. This revamp adds a heel tab and drops the Three-Stripes emblem. The Boost-enclosed midsole is paired with a herringbone-patterned rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Reflective
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Static Reflective' features the same look as the 'Static' colorway, but features reflective accents in the Primeknit yarns. The other details are the same as the 'Static', including a translucent side stripe and 3M reflective detailing on the shoe’s rope laces, Primeknit upper and Three-Stripes branding on the interior heel. The midsole makes use of ridged TPU sidewalls with semi-translucent properties, revealing full-length adidas Boost cushioning within. The 350 V2 'Static Reflective' is exclusive to Yeezy Supply.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Zyon’ retains the same material build as its full-sized counterpart. The sock-like construction adds a mix of grey and brown fibers to create unique woven patterns on the Off-White Primeknit upper, while the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe is rendered in a basic black. Semi-translucent rubber encases a full-length Boost midsole, good for responsive cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Reflective)
results.story: The momentum behind the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneaker began with its unveiling at the Yeezy Season 3 fashion show in 2016. This 'Lundmark Reflective' colorway was part of June 2019's regional-exclusive release and made available only to North and South American customers. The shoe includes a Primeknit upper that appears Off-White in daylight but reveals reflective details in dim conditions. This rendition ditches the style's typical heel tab but maintains the full-length adidas Boost cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016)
results.story: Released on February 15th, 2016, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 is identical to the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Pirate Black’ 2015 release except for its upgraded padding on the inside of the heel and softer suede on its branded medial patches. The design combines a pirate black/ dark grey Primeknit upper with patterned dark grey rope laces, red accents on the heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective)
results.story: The 'Antlia Reflective' colorway was offered as a part of a regional-exclusive launch, sold only in Europe on its release date in June 2019. The 350 V2 first debuted in 2016 as an update to the original 350, shown off at the Yeezy Season 3 fashion show. This model features a lighter take, casting the 350 V2 in a pale yellow-green hue. Its flexible Primeknit upper incorporates stunning reflective elements, and full-length adidas Boost cushioning provides a responsive feel from below.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Infant)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Infant ‘Orange’ showcases a vibrant finish on the minimalist polyester upper, accented with reflective 700 branding that dominates the sneaker’s lateral side panel. No-tie bungee laces deliver a snug fit, while a full-length drop-in Boost midsole offers lightweight and responsive cushioning. Underfoot, a grippy herringbone rubber outsole provides durable traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Infant)
results.story: Developed by Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneaker realizes the designer's usual subversive style. This edition—launched in July 2019—features a bicolor Primeknit bootie, integrated rope laces and tonal collar piping. A monofilament stripe runs the length of the lateral side and the signature heel strap has been excluded. Encased Boost technology with a semi-translucent rubber sole unit supports first steps.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant)
results.story: Released on August 24th, 2016, alongside the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Turtle Dove’ colorway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 is an exact replica of the adult model in infant sizes from 5 to 10. The design features a pirate black/dark grey Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Blue Tint
results.story: The 5th Yeezy to drop since November 2017 — Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Semi Frozen Yellow' and ‘Beluga 2.0,’ Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas, and the Yeezy 500 ‘Desert Rat’ — the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Blue Tint' was dropped on December 16th, 2017. The sneaker features a neutral white and grey upper with a red ‘SPLY-350’ text on the side in reverse. The shoe also comes with a heel tab, blue tint inner lining, and paste blue laces.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Tail Light
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Tail Light' showcases a pop of bright orange at the stitched textile heel tab, along with a less concentrated shade of the same hue on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The rest of the upper is constructed from light grey Primeknit in a minimalist one-piece build, complete with a distinctive center stitch running down the vamp. A semi-translucent rubber midsole houses adidas Boost cushioning for a smooth ride. The 'Tail Light' colorway is only available in Europe, Russia and Ukraine.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Kids)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Orange’ updates the retro-inspired silhouette with an eye-catching finish on the lightweight polyester upper. Reflective accents are littered throughout the minimalist design, including oversized ‘700’ branding emblazoned across the lateral side panel. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, visible through cut-outs in the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is iconic and highly coveted for its minimalist construction and reinvented heritage technology. Issued in September 2019, this edition benefits from a breathable Citrin Primeknit bootie styled with asymmetrical reflectivity, a see-through lateral stripe and Three-Stripes branding applied to the inner heel. A semi-translucent midsole carrying Boost tech and a gum rubber outsole form the underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeshaya Reflective' enhances the visual impact of the neutral two-tone Primeknit upper with reflective fibers woven into the build. Additional reflective hits appear on the rope laces and signature three-stripes that run down the interior of the rear collar, ultimately allowing the sneaker to shine in low-light conditions. A subtle yellow finish is applied to the semi-translucent rubber midsole, fitted with a Boost unit for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Hospital Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 is an ode to Kanye West's affinity for 90s running style with updated elements to place it in the modern world. Issued in September 2019, this 'Hospital Blue' version works a roller knit upper with leather overlays, mesh on the heel and reflective Three-Stripes across the sides. A sculpted midsole containing responsive Boost technology and a herringbone rubber outsole grant support and durability.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth (Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Synth Reflective' was designed by Kanye West for June 2019's batch of regional-exclusive releases. The 350 V2 began its legacy in 2016, when it was first seen on the runway at the Yeezy Season 3 fashion show. This model incorporates a Primeknit upper, ditching the heel tab once synonymous with the design. When hit with direct light, the shoe reveals powerful reflective detailing on the upper and laces. Full-length adidas Boost cushioning is reinforced by a rubber midsole/outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 OG Light Brown
results.story: Kanye West’s very first collaborative adidas shoe, the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘OG’ released worldwide February 2017 in extremely limited quantities. The towering boot-like builds showcases a radical departure from West’s previous designs, featuring a light brown all-suede upper mounted atop a partially ribbed, Boost-equipped rubber tooling in a subtle Off-White shade. The minimalist design is accented with oversized rope laces, perforated detailing on the toe box, and a wide midfoot strap in a tonal twill fabrication. A hidden zipper on the lateral side provides easy on and off.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infant)
results.story: Emerged in May 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 GID Infant 'Glow' sneaker is a high-vis execution of the cult icon. Its Primeknit bootie sports a fluorescent green hue that illuminates in the dark. Custom tooling comprises the heel pull, rope laces and a translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral side. Boost cushioning encased in a translucent rubber Tubular sole provides energized stability.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Yecheil’ enlivens the sneaker’s re-engineered Primeknit upper with a hectic mix of contrasting hues. A black monofilament side stripe adds a see-through element to the patchwork-like design, while reflective threads woven into the rope laces deliver enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A black rubber cage surrounds the full-length Boost midsole, good for responsive cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Pirate Black (W)
results.story: The women’s Yeezy 950 Boot in Pirate Black released in October 2015 as part of the Yeezy Season 1 drop. Made in collaboration with adidas, the 7-hole silhouette is inspired by a classic duck boot, featuring a combination of ballistic nylon and rubber. Premium suede is used on the eyestay and Yeezy tongue tag, while tonal eyelets and laces maintain the monochromatic design. A red topstitched heel tab offers a contrasting pop of color.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Lundmark Non-Reflective' sneaker brings together form and function, melding future-forward design and athletic performance. Unveiled in July 2019, this update presents a translucent monofilament stripe traversing the lateral of a duo-tone Primeknit upper. Patterned rope laces are integrated into the bootie. Underfoot, a semi-transparent tubular Boost-assisted sole provides energized cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infant ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ showcases a slip-on knit build with elastic lace closure for a snug fit. Orange and brown hues make up the camo-like design on the upper, accented with a contrasting royal blue streak on the translucent monofilament window. The minimalist sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent tan rubber cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sand Taupe’ delivers yet another in a long line of neutral colorways that have dominate the silhouette’s many releases since its global debut in 2016. Decorative no-tie laces are integrated into to the breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a patchwork-like pattern and a prominent seam that runs down the length of the vamp. On the lateral side panel, coral fibers are woven into the knit construction above the post-dyed monofilament side stripe for a subtle pop of color. A fully caged Boost midsole provides lightweight cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Yeshaya’ utilizes a simple grey and white color scheme on the breathable knit upper, rendered in different woven patterns for a patchwork-like effect. The same dual tones are applied to the heavy rope laces and signature monofilament side stripe, adding a see-through element to the lightweight design. A full-length Boost midsole, encased in pale yellow semi-translucent rubber, delivers a cushioned ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Stone
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Stone’ highlights subdued earth tones throughout its re-engineered Primeknit upper. The complementary blend of tan, brown and grey fibers is arranged in different weaves that create an intricate, patchwork-like design, offset by a coral-colored side stripe on the sneaker’s lateral side. The sock-like build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added durability and support. This colorway launched exclusively in Europe, Russia, Ukraine and the Asia-Pacific region.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga 2.0
results.story: With its name coming from the colorway similarities found on the first Yeezy Boost 350 V2, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Beluga 2.0' dropped on November 25, 2017. It was quickly restocked on November 30th after selling out. The shoe features a muted grey stripe on the laterals instead of the bright orange stripe found on the original ‘Beluga’ sneaker. The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Beluga 2.0' also features a heel pull tab with orange stitching and orange ‘SPLY-350’ lettering in reverse on the laterals.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Blue’ carries a re-engineered Primeknit upper constructed from a blend of slate blue, grey and black fibers. A pale yellow hue distinguishes the post-dyed monofilament side stripe woven into the sneaker’s lateral side panel, delivering added breathability and an unexpected pop of color. The sock-like upper rides on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped up in a semi-translucent rubber cage for improved stability and durability.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Ice’ represents one of four monochromatic colorways that collectively introduce a refreshed take on the minimalist silhouette. In lieu of traditional Primeknit, the upper is constructed from monofilament mesh, rendered in an icy blue shade and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. Additional details include an interior cage, webbing heel tab and molded eyelets. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids)
results.story: When the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Clay' debuted in late March, 2019, it marked the first time a 350 would be released in adult, kids and infant sizes. The kids'-sized Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Clay' maintains the same features as the adult version. The Primeknit upper comes in an orange-brown hue, with contrast patterns and a horizontal stripe. The bright orange heel tab adds a bit of pop, while the translucent midsole and rubber outsole finish out the look.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Antlia Non-Reflective' formats the June 2019 release for little feet. The 'Antlia' colorway, both in reflective and non-reflective iterations, was exclusively released in Europe. This infant-sized take includes a Primeknit upper with a semi-translucent window at the lateral, much like the original 350 V2 released in 2016. For an update, this shoe does without the heel tab and casts the upper in a pale yellow-green tone. Full-length Boost cushioning promotes comfort within a TPU cage, underscored by rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Desert Sage' is outfitted in a pale green Primeknit upper with tonal rope laces and reflective detailing on the sneaker’s signature side stripe. Contrast pops of color emerge on the orange collar lining and sockliner, the latter printed with dual adidas and Yeezy branding. The minimalist build sits atop full-length Boost midsole, encased in tonal green rubber with grippy gum rubber on the outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Infant)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Israfil’ features the same build as its full-sized counterpart, highlighted by a patchwork-like upper crafted from breathable Primeknit. The contrasting blend of pale yellow and bluish grey yarns is enlivened by a pop of orange on the signature side stripe that runs through the sneaker’s lateral side panel. A full-length Boost midsole is reinforced by durable semi-translucent rubber on all sides.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Kids)
results.story: The June 2019 release of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Antlia Non-Reflective' sees the design in a pale yellow-green hue. Reflective and non-reflective versions of the 'Antlia' were released exclusively in Europe. This kids' sized shoe stays close to the design of 2016's 350 V2, with a flexible Primeknit upper and semi-translucent window, but drops the typical heel tab. Every step is cushioned with full-length Boost cushioning within a TPU cage for a responsive feel, finished off with rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is the fifth installment of Kanye West's line with the German sportswear brand, making its first appearance in the Yeezy Season 3 show. Launched in December 2019, this Yecheil update revises the template in multi-color Primeknit re-engineered with reflective threading across the profile and laces. The transparent monofilament stripe is woven into the lateral side. A black Tubular sole utilizes full-length Boost technology.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Infant ‘Bone’ utilizes a one-piece polyester upper secured with no-tie bungee laces, enabling convenient and easy on and off for little feet. The understated color scheme is enlivened with reflective silver accents, highlighted by 700 branding on the sneaker’s lateral side. A sculpted PU midsole in contrasting black houses a full-length Boost unit, visible through cut-outs in the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Israfil’ features a breathable Primeknit upper that combines a blend of yarns in pale yellow and bluish-grey hues, rendered in different woven patterns for a patchwork-like effect. A post-dyed monofilament side stripe in orange delivers a pop of color on the sneaker’s lateral side. Secured with elastic no-tie laces, the minimalist silhouette rides on a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced with a semi-translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeezreel (Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeezreel' is a vibrant rework of the Kanye West-designed sneaker. Arrived in December 2019, it comes with reflective threads woven into the split-colored neon Primeknit upper and rope laces. A post-dyed monofilament side stripe cuts through the lateral. Full-length Boost cushioning technology can be viewed through the glow-in-the-dark midsole and rubber sole unit below.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ showcases clashing hues throughout the breathable Primeknit upper. A streak of royal blue stands out on the translucent monofilament window woven into the side panel, contrasted by a blend of orange and brown hues arranged in a camo-like pattern. The lightweight build is supported by a Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Bone’ features a tan polyester upper, accented on the lateral side panel with oversized 700 branding in a reflective silver finish. The lightweight build is secured with no-tie bungee laces, while contrasting black overlays provide added durability. A matching black PU midsole houses full-length drop-in Boost cushioning, visible underfoot through cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Max Infuriate 2 Low EP 'Yeezy'
results.story: The Nike Air Max Infuriate 2 Low EP is a performance-ready shoe built for agility and power. Designed with the Nike tech of previous models, this 'Yeezy' edition is rendered with breathable, abrasion-resistant mesh with integrated Flywire cables and fused eyestays. A bright sockliner and an oversized forefoot Swoosh adds distinction to the monochromatic look. This update sits on a high-profile, two-tone midsole with a visible heel Air unit.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Triple Black’ delivers a monochromatic take on Kanye West’s maximalist lifestyle runner. The upper, built with lightweight polyester and synthetic no-sew overlays, features reflective detailing throughout, including the oversized 700 branding that adorns the sneaker’s side panels. No-tie bungee laces provide a snug fit, while a full-length drop-in Boost midsole is good for a responsive ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant adapts Kanye West's groundbreaking design—initially launched in September 2016—in a kid-friendly build. Revealed in September 2019, this Citrin variant boasts a non-reflective Primeknit bootie featuring an asymmetrical stitch pattern, integrated lacing and a post-dyed translucent stripe across the lateral side. Infused with energy-filled Boost technology, the two-tone sole completes the look.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Pearl’ applies contrast color blocking to the re-engineered Primeknit upper. Most of the knit build features a blend of indigo, grey and navy fibers, while the top half of the sneaker’s lateral side is rendered in subtle cream and beige tones. The latter hue is repeated on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The lightweight sneaker is supported by a full-length Boost midsole, its sidewalls reinforced with an off-white rubber cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Phosphor’ applies a neon yellow finish to a one-piece polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and fortified with contrasting black-no sew overlays. The two-tone color scheme is accented by reflective silver detailing, highlighted by oversized 700 branding on the lateral side panel. A sculpted PU midsole packs a full-length drop-in Boost unit for lightweight and responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Kids)
results.story: First introduced as part of the Season 3 collection, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids returns Kanye West's iconic design with pared-down styling. This Citrin version—revealed in September 2019—serves up a non-reflective Primeknit bootie teamed with integrated lacing and the signature translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral. A two-tone Tubular rubber outsole, assisted by responsive Boost technology, is placed below.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infants ‘Carbon’ delivers an entirely neutral colorway of the minimalist sneaker, supported by a full-length Boost midsole encased in semi-translucent rubber. Up top, breathable Primeknit construction blends black, grey and tan yarns for a unique patchwork-like aesthetic. Details include black no-tie elastic laces and a post-dyed monofilament side stripe in a matching black finish.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Yeshaya’ delivers a neutral take on the minimalist lifestyle silhouette, featuring a mix of different woven patterns throughout the breathable Primeknit upper. The grey and white patchwork-like design is mounted atop a full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber cage in an Off-White finish. A grippy gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth (Non-Reflective)
results.story: Through the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Synth Non-Reflective,' Kanye West continues the 350 V2's legacy, which began in 2016. This model was offered as a regional-exclusive release, made available to customers only in Africa, Asia and Australia. The shoe incorporates a flexible Primeknit upper with a semi-translucent window at the lateral, dropping the heel tab usually associated with the style. Full-length adidas Boost is encapsulated by a TPU midsole cage, underscored by gum rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Desert Sage’ features a subtle green hue on the lightweight Primeknit upper, accented with a reflective monofilament side stripe and a contrasting pop of orange on the collar. A brighter shade of green is applied to the semi-translucent rubber cage that surrounds the full-length Boost midsole, exposed underfoot through cut-out detailing on the pale orange rubber outsole.
